     In CSS, a SPACE ( ) is a powerful connector. It means: 
     "Look for the target element INSIDE or NESTED WITHIN the parent element."
     
  2. BREAKING DOWN "div li":
     • div   : The starting point (The parent/ancestor container).
     • [ ]   : The space means "go inside" or "search within the universe of this div".
     • li    : The final target (The child/descendant element we want to find).
     
     So, "div li" translates to: "Find all <li> tags that live inside a <div> tag."

