      - Relying solely on page.waitForLoadState("networkidle") can be unstable under heavy server traffic.
      - Even if network calls finish, heavy assets (like product images) might still delay the rendering of cards.
      - If the test attempts to count titles before full rendering, it returns 0 elements and fails.
      - FIX: Explicitly wait for a specific element to load (e.g., the first card body or title) using '.waitFor()' 
        before performing actions or gathering array data.

