   - Selector: ".react-calendar__navigation__label" (CSS Class)
   - Reason: Clicks the top header button twice to zoom out the view.
     * 1st Click: Changes view from Days -> Months
     * 2nd Click: Changes view from Months -> Years (Decade Grid)
   
3. Select Year:
   - Locator: page.getByText(year) (Playwright Text Locator)
   - Reason: Dynamically searches the screen for the target year string (e.g. "2026") and clicks it.
   
4. Select Month:
   - Selector: ".react-calendar__year-view__months__month" (CSS Class)
   - Logic: This class returns an array of all 12 month buttons. 
     * JavaScript arrays are 0-indexed (January = 0, February = 1 ... July = 6).
     * Formula: We use '.nth(Number(month) - 1)' to click the correct index (e.g., Month 7 - 1 = Index 6).

5. Select Day:
   - Selector: "//abbr[text()='" + day + "']" (Dynamic XPath)
   - Formula: //tagname[text()='value']
   - Reason: Specifically targets an <abbr> tag with the exact day text to avoid clicking any duplicate numbers on the page.


